.TH calculate_noise_margin  22.14 "Fri Oct 06 02:12:27 2023" 
.SH Name \fBcalculate_noise_margin\fR \-  Specifies to calculate noise margins with worst voltages on the driver-receiver pins
.SH Syntax  \fBcalculate_noise_margin\fR  [-help]   -noise_limit_file <input_file>  -power_directory <dir>  -state_directory <dir> 
.P Specifies to calculate noise margins with worst voltages on the driver-receiver pins. To run this command, you need to specify the default or cell-specific noise limit, signal noise, guardband, rail directory, and power directory. Before running the calculate_noise_margin command, you need to specify the set_power_analysis_mode -create_driver_db true parameter to generate the driver-receiver database.
.P The use model of the command is:  set_power_analysis_mode
... -create_driver_db true  calculate_noise_margin -noise_limit_file <input_file> -state_directory <dir> -power_directory <file>
.P The command generates the noise margin output file in the state directory. The format of the noise margin output file (<powernetname_groundnetname>.noise_margin) is:  Margin_High(V)Margin_Low(V)NMH(V)NMI(V)Voh(V)Vol(V)Vih(V)Vil(V)Signal_Noise(V)Guardband(V)Dr Inst/pinRx Inst/pin  "\fBNMH - signal noise - guardband\fR" NMI - signal noise - guardband  Voh - Vih  Vil - Vol  VDD_driver - VSS_receiver  VSS_driver - VSS_receiver  (1-noise_limit)*(VDD_receiver - VSS_receiver)  noise_limit is the noise limit value specified in the noise limit file  noise_limit*(VDD_receiver - VSS_receiver)  noise_limit is the noise limit value specified in the noise limit file Signal noise value specified in the noise limit file  Guardband value specified in the noise limit file  Driver pin name  Receiver pin name
.P 
.SH Parameters    "\fB-help\fR" Prints a brief description that includes the type and default information for each calculate_noise_margin parameter.  For a detailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use the man command:  man calculate_noise_margin  "\fB-noise_limit_file <input_file>\fR" Specifies the name of the input noise limit file that contains the default or cell-specific noise limit, signal noise, and guardband. The format of the noise limit file is:  default_noise_limit <<value>>  default_signal_noise <<value>>  default_guard_band <<value>>  <<cell_name>> <<noise_limit>> <<signal_noise>> <<guard_band>>  The following is a snippet of the noise limit file:  default_noise_limit 0.46  default_signal_noise 0.1  default_guard_band 0.05  "\fB-power_directory <dir>\fR" Specifies the path to the power directory to access driver-receiver pairs.   "\fB-state_directory <dir>\fR" Specifies the path to the state directory generated by rail analysis to access EIV database. 
.SH Examples
.RS  "*" 2 The following command calculates noise margin:   calculate_noise_margin -noise_limit_file
./noiselimit -state_directory dynamic_rail/core_105C_dynamic_1 -power_directory dynamic_power
.RE 
.SH Related Information
.RS  "*" 2 set_rail_analysis_mode  "*" 2 calculate_differential_voltage   "*" 2 "Static Power, IRdrop and EM Analysis" in the Voltus IC Power Integrity Solution User Guide
.RE
.P
